<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="544" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Combs</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-18"><hi rend="italic">July 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Had an interview with President of Peru and minister for foreign affairs
                            of Peru at their request this afternoon, to explain the effect of
                            congressional action required in protocol. Convinced them such action
                            wise and necessary. Both undertook unequivocal and hearty approval and
                            support of protocol.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Combs.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>